  "prompt": "How do I get funds for a startup company?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to get funds for a startup:\n\n1. Personal Savings\n- Use your own money\n- Low risk, full control\n\n2. Friends and Family\n- Loans or investments\n- Often more flexible terms\n\n3. Angel Investors\n- High net-worth individuals\n- Provide capital for equity\n\n4. Venture Capital\n- Professional investment firms\n- Typically for high-growth potential businesses\n\n5. Crowdfunding\n- Platforms like Kickstarter\n- Raise small amounts from many people\n\n6. Small Business Loans\n- Bank loans\n- Government-backed SBA loans\n\n7. Grants\n- Government or private organization grants\n- Often industry-specific\n\n8. Incubators and Accelerators\n- Provide funding and mentorship\n- Help develop business strategy\n\n9. Corporate Partnerships\n- Larger companies investing in startups\n- Can provide funding and resources\n\n10. Pitch Competitions\n- Win funding through business competitions\n- Opportunity to network\n\n11. Online Lending Platforms\n- Alternative lending sources\n- Faster application process\n\n12. Pre-sales or Bootstrapping\n- Generate initial revenue before seeking external funding\n- Demonstrate market viability\n\nChoose methods that align with your business model and growth strategy.",
